document_data.History:
In [[1370 DR]], Shoudra was ordered by Marchion [[Elastul Raurym]] to travel to [[Mithral Hall]] with the [[gnome]] [[Nanfoodle]] to sabotage the industry there.

Shortly thereafter, their plan was uncovered by Steward [[Regis]] of [[Mithral Hall]] after he enchanted Nanfoodle with his [[ruby pendant]]. Shoudra defended themselves, saying that had they known that Mithral Hall was at war with the [[orc]] tribes, they would not have attempted to poison the ore. Shoudra and Nanfoodle then aided Mithral Hall in its war efforts.{{cite book/The Hunters Blades trilogy|698}}

Soon after, at the battle of Mithral Hall's eastern gates, Shoudra was hoisted into the air by King [[Obould|Obould Many-Arrow]]s and sliced in half with his flaming greatsword.
